The paper proposes a neural network-based model for Reading Comprehension with Multiple Choice Questions, which is a task commonly studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The model uses gates to eliminate options and refine the passage representation, which involves techniques such as attention and orthogonalization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP and information retrieval. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are also relevant to the paper's methodology and applications.
